<h2 id="what-is-gohighlevel">🏥 What Is GoHighLevel?</h2>

GoHighLevel (GHL) is an all-in-one sales and marketing platform that consolidates CRM, email marketing, SMS campaigns, appointment booking, reputation management, and funnel building into a single dashboard. Originally built for marketing agencies, it's evolved into a powerhouse for service businesses—particularly med spas and aesthetic practices that live and die by their lead pipeline.

What makes GHL different from platforms like HubSpot or Salesforce isn't raw feature count. It's the combination of unlimited sub-accounts at the Agency level and white-label capabilities that let operators standardize systems across multiple locations without per-seat licensing bleeding them dry.

For med spas specifically, the platform shines in three areas: automated lead nurturing sequences, two-way SMS conversations that actually get responses, and the reactivation workflows that bring dormant patients back through the door. In 2026, GHL has doubled down on AI-powered conversation tools that handle initial lead qualification without human intervention.

<h2 id="our-experience">📊 Our Experience Managing Med Spa Tech Stacks</h2>

Our team has evaluated and deployed marketing platforms across hundreds of med spa locations over the past decade. We've watched operators blow $50,000 on enterprise CRMs that sat unused because front desk staff couldn't navigate them. We've seen practices limp along with spreadsheets and sticky notes until their lead database became an archaeological dig.

GoHighLevel entered our radar around 2021 when a 12-location med spa group asked us to audit their tech stack. They were paying $2,400/month across four different platforms—separate tools for email, SMS, booking, and reputation management. We consolidated everything into GHL at $297/month total. Within 90 days, they'd reactivated 847 dormant patients and booked $127,000 in treatments from people who hadn't walked through the door in 18+ months.

