The operators who struggle? Usually practices under $500K annual revenue trying to DIY implementation while also running clinical operations. GHL rewards investment in setup—either time or money hiring someone to configure it right.

<h2 id="key-features">⚡ Key Features for Med Spa Operators</h2>

<h3 id="lead-reactivation-workflows">Lead Reactivation Workflows</h3>

This is where GHL earns its keep for med spas. The platform's workflow builder lets you create multi-step reactivation campaigns that trigger based on last appointment date, treatment type, or spending history. A typical sequence we deploy hits dormant patients with a personalized SMS, follows up with an email showcasing before/after results, and escalates to a phone task for your patient coordinator if there's no response.

In 2026, GHL's AI conversation feature can now handle the initial text exchange. When a dormant patient responds "interested but busy," the AI recognizes this isn't a hard no and keeps the conversation warm until they're ready to book. Our clients report 30-40% of reactivations now happen through AI-handled text threads.

The key metric we track: dormant patient reactivation rate. Across our med spa clients using GHL, we see 18-22% of patients who haven't visited in 12+ months booking within 60 days of entering a reactivation workflow. At an average ticket of $400-600 for aesthetic treatments, that math gets compelling fast.

<h3 id="two-way-sms-conversations">Two-Way SMS & Conversation Management</h3>

Med spa patients don't answer phone calls. They barely check email. But they'll respond to a text within minutes. GHL's conversation view consolidates all communication channels—SMS, email, Facebook Messenger, Instagram DMs, Google Business Messages—into a single inbox your team can manage without tab-switching chaos.

The 2026 update added intelligent conversation routing, so messages from high-value patients (based on spending history) automatically surface at the top. This matters when you're running 500+ active conversations across locations and need to prioritize the patient considering a $15,000 full-face rejuvenation package over someone asking about your hours.

<h3 id="appointment-booking">Integrated Appointment Booking</h3>

GHL's calendar system won't replace specialized med spa scheduling software like Boulevard or Mangomint for complex resource management. But for marketing-driven bookings—consults, follow-ups, promotional appointments—it handles the job without forcing leads to leave your funnel.

The calendar syncs with Google and Outlook, supports multiple team members, and integrates directly with your automation workflows. When a lead books a consult, they automatically enter your pre-appointment nurture sequence. No manual enrollment, no dropped balls.

For deeper scheduling insights, check out our <a href="/reviews/boulevard-vs-mangomint-2026">Boulevard vs Mangomint comparison</a> covering the scheduling platforms purpose-built for med spas.

<h3 id="reputation-management">Reputation Management</h3>

Google reviews directly impact whether new patients find you. GHL automates review requests post-appointment, routes positive reviewers to Google while capturing negative feedback privately for service recovery. The 2026 platform includes sentiment analysis that flags concerning reviews for immediate response.

Our recommendation: tie review requests to specific high-satisfaction touchpoints. Don't blast every patient—target those who received popular treatments with historically high satisfaction scores.

<h3 id="funnel-builder">Funnel & Landing Page Builder</h3>

Building treatment-specific landing pages inside GHL keeps your lead capture, CRM, and follow-up in one ecosystem. The drag-and-drop builder won't win design awards, but it produces functional pages that convert. For med spas running seasonal promotions or new treatment launches, spinning up a dedicated landing page with integrated booking takes 30 minutes, not days of back-and-forth with developers.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Build a "treatment interest" tag system from day one. When leads click specific treatment links or visit certain pages, tag them accordingly. Your reactivation campaigns become dramatically more effective when you're texting past patients about treatments they've already expressed interest in—not generic "we miss you" messages.
</div>

