<h2 id="implementation-reality">🛠️ Implementation Reality Check</h2>

Let's be direct: GHL implementations fail more often than they succeed, and it's rarely the platform's fault. Operators buy it, poke around for a week, get overwhelmed by the workflow builder, and let the subscription run while returning to their old ways.

Successful deployments share a pattern. First, you migrate your existing patient database with clean data—no duplicate records, no missing contact info. Second, you build one workflow that addresses your biggest pain point, usually appointment reminders or immediate lead response. Get that working and proving ROI before expanding. Third, you assign a specific person to own GHL operations. This isn't a side task; it requires 5-10 hours weekly once you're past initial setup.

Our team recommends most med spas budget $2,000-5,000 for professional implementation if you don't have internal bandwidth. That upfront investment pays back within months when your reactivation campaigns actually run instead of sitting half-built in your account.

